## 2026-06-30 - Task 1 AuthProvider lint-safe loading initialization

- The `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect` lint rule catches synchronous `setState` calls both in the main effect body and inside `catch` blocks within the effect.
- Smallest safe fix: initialize `loading` from `isFirebaseConfigured` so the unconfigured path never needs a synchronous `setLoading(false)` in the effect, and defer the listener-init-error `setLoading(false)` with `queueMicrotask`.
- Mocking a module-level boolean for test permutations requires a getter in `vi.mock` so `beforeEach` mutations are visible at render time (mock factories are evaluated once, but getters read the hoisted mutable object on each access).
